<H3> <TI>   Dutch Prime Minister Arrives on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dutch Prime Minister Arrives on Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1904172194 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1420 GMT 19 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1904172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest ROMPRES</LOCATION>, 19/4/1994 -- A government 
delegation from the <LOCATION>Netherlands</LOCATION> headed by Prime Minister <PERSON>Ruud 
Lubbers</PERSON> arrived in <LOCATION>Bucharest</LOCATION> on <DATE>Tuesday, April 19</DATE>, for a two-day 
official visit. The Dutch guests were greeted at the <LOCATION>Otopeni 
Airport</LOCATION> by Romanian Prime Minister <PERSON>Nicolae Vacaroiu</PERSON>, Foreign 
Minister <PERSON>Teodor Melescanu</PERSON>, Minister of State <PERSON>Dan Mircea Popescu</PERSON>, 
the Dutch ambassador in <LOCATION>Bucharest</LOCATION>, <PERSON>Monique Frank</PERSON>, and other 
officials. 
  Shortly after his arrival, Premier <PERSON>Ruud Lubbers</PERSON> said that 
his 
visit in <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> would further substantiate the cooperation 
between the two countries. The <LOCATION>Netherlands</LOCATION> is located on the 
other side of <LOCATION>Europe</LOCATION> and considers that transports and trade are 
especially important, said the Dutch prime minister and added 
that the <LOCATION>Rhine</LOCATION>- Main-Danube watercourse would ease the bilateral 
ties, as <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> is located on the other end of the road and 
therefore the bilateral cooperation was extremely necessary, not 
only in the economic field but also in the political one and 
perhaps also in tourism. The Dutch premier mentioned the 
Latin-rooted language spoken by Romanians as a very special 
trait of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> in <LOCATION>central Europe</LOCATION>. 
  On <DATE>Wednesday</DATE> [20 <DATE>April</DATE>], Premier <PERSON>Ruud Lubbers</PERSON> is scheduled 
to 
meet <ORGANIZATION>Romanian Senate</ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON>Oliviu Gherman</PERSON>, Chamber of 
Deputies' Speaker <PERSON>Adrian Nastase</PERSON>, the presidential adviser <PERSON>Misu 
Negritoiu</PERSON>, and the governor of the <ORGANIZATION>National Bank of Romania</ORGANIZATION>, 
<PERSON>Mugur Isarescu</PERSON>. 
  Today <PERSON>Ruud Lubbers</PERSON> was received by Romanian President <PERSON>Ion 
Iliescu</PERSON>, at <ORGANIZATION>Cotroceni Palace</ORGANIZATION>. The Dutch guest was accompanied 
by Dutch Foreign Affairs Minister <PERSON>Peter Kooijmans</PERSON>. The visit of 
the high Dutch officials is the first of its kind since 
<LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>'s <DATE>December 1989</DATE> revolution. 
  The interview was attended by <ORGANIZATION>Romanian Minister of Foreign 
Affairs Teodor Melescanu</ORGANIZATION>, Minister of State <PERSON>Dan Mircea Popescu</PERSON>, 
presidential advisers <PERSON>Misu Negritoiu</PERSON> and <PERSON>Traian Chebeleu</PERSON>, the 
Romanian ambassador to the <LOCATION>Netherlands</LOCATION>, <PERSON>Marin Buhoara</PERSON>. 
  After the official talks, the Romanian president gave his 
guests lunch. 

</TEXT>

