<H3> <TI>   U.S. General Continues Visit, Talks on NATO </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. General Continues Visit, Talks on NATO </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Talks With Tinca Reported </H4>

<F P=102> AU0604153794 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1202 GMT 6 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0604153794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest ROMPRES</LOCATION>, 6/4/1994 -- <DATE>Wednesday</DATE>, 6 <DATE>April</DATE>, 
the talks started between Romanian Defense Minister <PERSON>Gheorghe 
Tinca</PERSON> and General <PERSON>George Joulwan</PERSON>, supreme commander of the 
allied forces in <LOCATION>Europe</LOCATION>, who is now on a documentation visit in 
<LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>. The agenda, <ORGANIZATION>Romanian Army</ORGANIZATION> sources say, includes 
matters related to the participation of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> and other East 
European countries in the Partnership for Peace program, the 
evolution of the democratic process in <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> and the parallel 
reform of the army, to matters concerning European and 
international security. 
  Attending the talks are <PERSON>Dumitru Cioflina</PERSON>, secretary of state 
at the <ORGANIZATION>National Defense Ministry</ORGANIZATION> and chief of the general staff, 
<PERSON>Ioan Mircea Pascu</PERSON>, secretary of state for defense policies and 
external relations of the <ORGANIZATION>National Defense Ministry</ORGANIZATION>, and other 
military officials accompanying the guest. 
  In the morning of 6 <DATE>April</DATE> General <PERSON>George Joulwan</PERSON> was 
received 
by the president of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Ion Iliescu</LOCATION>. 

</TEXT>

