<H3> <TI>   UDMR Walks Out of Senate Over Veterans' Bill </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203143494 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1230 GMT 22 Mar 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2203143494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest</LOCATION>, ROMPRES 22/3/1994 -- The <ORGANIZATION>Senate</ORGANIZATION> resumed 
<DATE>Tuesday</DATE>, <DATE>March 22</DATE>, the debates of the bill on war veterans and 
widows. The parliamentary group of the <ORGANIZATION>Hungarian Democratic 
Union</ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION>UDMR</ORGANIZATION>, asked for permission to make a political 
declaration on part of the articles of the said bill. Submitted 
to vote, the request was rejected. Consequently the members of 
the <ORGANIZATION>UDMR</ORGANIZATION> parliamentary group walked out of the <ORGANIZATION>Senate Hall</ORGANIZATION>. 
  The <ORGANIZATION>Senate</ORGANIZATION> passed in its <DATE>Monday</DATE>, <DATE>March 21</DATE> sitting an 
amendment to an article of the bill on war veterans and widows 
saying that the residents of Romanian territories occupied over 
1940-1945, that were called to arms fight in the Armies of other 
states are considered to be war veterans only "if they did not 
fight against the <ORGANIZATION>Romanian Army</ORGANIZATION>." The members of the <ORGANIZATION>UDMR</ORGANIZATION> group 
opposed the amendment. 

</TEXT>

