<H3> <TI>   Holds Talks With Iliescu </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Holds Talks With Iliescu </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1904171994 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1248 GMT 19 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1904171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest ROMPRES</LOCATION>, 19/4/1994 -- The minister of 
foreign affairs of the Republic of <LOCATION>Armenia</LOCATION>, <PERSON>Vahan Papazyan</PERSON>, was 
received on <DATE>Tuesday, April 19</DATE>, at the <ORGANIZATION>Cotroceni Palace</ORGANIZATION>, by 
Romanian President <PERSON>Ion Iliescu</PERSON>. 
  In a statement to the press made at the end of the 
interview, 
the Armenian chief diplomat underscored the necessity of 
developing the bilateral relations as the main subject of his 
dialogue with the Romanian head of state along with an analysis 
of several issues of the international life, especially the 
situation in <LOCATION>Nagorno</LOCATION>- <LOCATION>Karabakh</LOCATION> and in <LOCATION>Bosnia-Herzegovina</LOCATION> as 
<LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Armenia</LOCATION> were equally interested in their settlement. 
The Armenian minister of foreign affairs delivered to the 
Romanian president a message from the part of the Armenian 
president together with the invitation to visit <LOCATION>Armenia</LOCATION>. 
  The interview was attended also by Romanian Foreign Minister 
<PERSON>Teodor Melescanu</PERSON>, Presidential Adviser <PERSON>Traian Chebeleu</PERSON> and 
<PERSON>Varujan Vosganian</PERSON>, deputy in the Romanian Parliament 
representing the Armenian minority of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>. 
  Armenian ambassador <PERSON>Guergui Kazinyan</PERSON> [name as received] 
presented on <DATE>Monday, April 18</DATE>, his credentials while the 
<ORGANIZATION>Armenian Embassy</ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION>Bucharest</LOCATION> is going to be officially opened 
within the following days. 

</TEXT>

