<H3> <TI>   German Parliamentary Delegation To Assess Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    German Parliamentary Delegation To Assess Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405181094 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1410 GMT 4 May 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0405181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest ROMPRES</LOCATION>, 4/5/1994 -- The parliamentary 
secretary of state of the <ORGANIZATION>German Ministry of the Interior</ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON>Horst 
Waffenschmidt</PERSON>, in charge with the affairs of the Germans abroad, 
started on <DATE>Wednesday</DATE> a three-day visit in <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> accompanied by 
a delegation comprising deputies in the <LOCATION>Bundestag</LOCATION>, the 
presidents of the associations of the Swabians and the Saxons of 
<LOCATION>Germany</LOCATION>, representatives of charity institutions, government 
dignitaries, said <ORGANIZATION>Romanian Foreign Ministry</ORGANIZATION> spokesperson <PERSON>Simona 
Miculescu</PERSON> at a press conference on <DATE>Wednesday</DATE>. The visit is 
meant to assess the aid granted by the German Government to the 
German nationals of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> in order to decide over new measures 
of aid in the economic, cultural, social and education fields. 
The German delegation will be received by Romanian President 
<PERSON>Ion Iliescu</PERSON> and will have talks with members of the <ORGANIZATION>Romanian 
Government</ORGANIZATION>. 
  The <ORGANIZATION>Foreign Ministry</ORGANIZATION> spokesperson said also that the German 
minister for economic cooperation Carl-Dieter Spranger would 
visit <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> on <DATE>May 6-7</DATE> at the invitation of the <ORGANIZATION>Romanian 
Government</ORGANIZATION> in order work out new actions of German support to 
the economic restructuring process in <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> especially in the 
industrial sector. On that occasion, a governmental 
frame-agreement will be signed concerning the technological 
cooperation between <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Germany</LOCATION>. 

</TEXT>

