<H3> <TI>   Defense Official on Danger of `Subversion' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Official on Danger of `Subversion' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1604154494 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1543 GMT 15 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1604154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest ROMPRES</LOCATION>, 15/4/1994 -- The main danger 
threatening <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> is not coming from outside, but rather from 
inside, subversion being one of its forms, <PERSON>Ion Mircea Pascu</PERSON>, 
secretary of state in charge of defense and international 
relations of the <ORGANIZATION>Romanian Ministry of Defense</ORGANIZATION>, told a news 
conference <DATE>Friday, 15 April</DATE>. Subversive acts can be 'canvassed' 
in many ways, he said, by those who pursue such aims. <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> 
does not exclude extraneous danger, although this is less 
poignant at the moment. He said <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>'s option is for 
integration in the European structures, and that the Partnership 
for Peace is one step towards that goal. <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>'s ultimate 
target in its strive for integration is the forging of a 
European security system comprising all the actors on the 
European political stage, the <ORGANIZATION>Russian Federation</ORGANIZATION>, the <LOCATION>Ukraine</LOCATION>, 
the <LOCATION>United States</LOCATION>, and <LOCATION>Canada</LOCATION>, inclusively. 
  Related to the problems the <ORGANIZATION>Romanian Army</ORGANIZATION> is confronted 
with, 
the secretary of state said its endowment and equipment shall be 
done as the budget allocation permits. Although modest, this 
provides for certain growths which will enable the army to 
upgrade medical assistance and housing conditions for the 
military. 

</TEXT>

