<H3> <TI>   Armenia's Papazyan Arrives, Meets Melescanu </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenia's Papazyan Arrives, Meets Melescanu </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1804165194 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1421 GMT 18 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1804165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest ROMPRES</LOCATION>, 18/4/1994 -- "The talks between 
the foreign ministers of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Armenia</LOCATION> pointed to the 
necessity of concluding the soonest a basic political treaty 
between the two countries," said <ORGANIZATION>Romanian Foreign Ministry</ORGANIZATION> 
Spokesman <PERSON>Mircea Geoana</PERSON> at the close of the first round of talks 
between <PERSON>Teodor Melescanu</PERSON> and <PERSON>Vahan Papazyan</PERSON>. It is hoped that 
in a near future that important document will be signed during a 
meeting of the two countries' presidents. 
  The parties informed each other on the situation in Trans- 
Caucasian and the conflict in former <LOCATION>Yugoslavia</LOCATION>. Papazyan 
referred to the conflict in <LOCATION>Nagorno Karabakh</LOCATION> and outlined the 
latest developments and initiatives for its settlement. Teodor 
Melescanu outlined <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>'s main foreign policy options. He 
presented the stage of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>'s relations with the <ORGANIZATION>NATO</ORGANIZATION>, the 
<LOCATION>European Union</LOCATION>, and the neighboring states. 
  During the talks the parties agreed to expand the relations 
of cooperation in the international bodies, especially the <ORGANIZATION>CSCE</ORGANIZATION> 
and the <ORGANIZATION>UN</ORGANIZATION>, and at a subregional level, with reference to the 
Black Sea area. 

</TEXT>

