<H3> <TI>   Meets With President Iliescu </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets With President Iliescu </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0906183294 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1749 GMT 9 Jun 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0906183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest ROMPRES</LOCATION>, 9/6/1994 -- Romanian President 
<PERSON>Ion Iliescu</PERSON> received <DATE>Thursday</DATE>, 9 <DATE>June</DATE>, the Chinese minister of 
the machine-building industry He Guangyuan, head of his 
country's delegation to the 12th session of the <ORGANIZATION>Romanian-Chinese 
Joint Governmental Committee on Economic and Technical 
Cooperation</ORGANIZATION>, held these days in <LOCATION>Bucharest</LOCATION>. 
  At the close of the interview, the guest was appreciative of 
the progress made by the Romanian-Chinese relations, and quoted 
President Iliescu as saying that the Romanian side hoped the 
economic cooperation with <LOCATION>China</LOCATION> would open better trade 
opportunities to Romanian and Chinese firms. Minister <PERSON>Guangyuan</PERSON> 
anticipated that the visit of Premier <PERSON>Li Peng</PERSON> next month to 
<LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> will give a greater impetus to the relations between the 
two countries. 

</TEXT>

