<H3> <TI>   Minister Views Economic Reform, Privatization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Views Economic Reform, Privatization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1005162794 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 0926 GMT 10 May 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1005162794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest</LOCATION>, ROMPRES, 10/5/1994 -- Romanian Minister 
of State <PERSON>Mircea Cosea</PERSON> appreciated as a success the stabilization 
of the leu exchange rate reached in <DATE>April</DATE> as much valuable as it 
had been achieved without "traumas or big commotions." In an 
interview with the <ORGANIZATION>Romania Radio</ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON>Vacaroiu</PERSON> cabinet's reform 
minister <PERSON>Mircea Cosea</PERSON> said the stabilization process would 
continue till <DATE>June</DATE>, the current year, when the inter-bank market 
is scheduled to be established. Cosea opined the success 
belonged to a fruitful cooperation between <ORGANIZATION>Government</ORGANIZATION> and the 
<ORGANIZATION>National Bank of Romania</ORGANIZATION> "extremely well valued abroad" and the 
"final" condition on the <ORGANIZATION>IMF</ORGANIZATION> stand-by loan. 
  Referring to the stage of privatization, <PERSON>Cosea</PERSON> said the 
so-called "<PERCENT>30 percent</PERCENT>" action would be finalized within the 
current month. The action will consist in the population's 
exchanging their property certificates -- previously granted to 
the population -- for shares in the commercial state companies 
amounting up to a total value of <PERCENT>30 percent</PERCENT> of the commercial 
companies' aggregate capital. The <ORGANIZATION>Governmental Council of 
Economic Coordination</ORGANIZATION>, Strategy, and Reform -- headed by <PERSON>Cosea</PERSON> 
-- together with the <ORGANIZATION>National Privatization Agency</ORGANIZATION>, State 
Property Fund, and the (five) Private Property Funds are drawing 
up the details of the stock public offering. 
  <PERSON>Mircea Cosea</PERSON> gave as a proof of the increasing international 
recognition of the economic reform in <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> the invitation he 
had received in order to open and lead a conference organized by 
the specialized commission of the <LOCATION>European Union</LOCATION> for issues 
concerning the small and middle-sized enterprises. 

</TEXT>

