<H3> <TI>   Court Backs Campeanu's Claim to PNL Leadership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Court Backs Campeanu's Claim to PNL Leadership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405115594 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 0955 GMT 4 May 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0405115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest ROMPRES</LOCATION>, 4/5/1994 -- <PERSON>Radu Campeanu</PERSON> has 
been acknowledged as legitimate president of the <ORGANIZATION>National 
Liberal Party</ORGANIZATION> (PNL) by virtue of a court sentence passed 
yesterday, 3 <DATE>May</DATE>, by the <ORGANIZATION>Bucharest Municipal Court</ORGANIZATION>, which ruled 
against a similar claim by the group led by <PERSON>Mircea 
Ionescu-Quintus</PERSON>. 
  The conflict between the two factions of the <ORGANIZATION>PNL</ORGANIZATION>, generated 
by the wish to reign supreme in the liberal movement, opposes 
<PERSON>Radu Campeanu</PERSON>, liberal member in the <DATE>1940</DATE>'s, repatriated in <DATE>1990</DATE> 
after years of residence in <LOCATION>France</LOCATION>, who held the <ORGANIZATION>PNL</ORGANIZATION> 
chairmanship over 1990-1993, and ran for the presidency of 
<LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> in <DATE>1990</DATE>, to <PERSON>Mircea Ionescu-Quintus</PERSON>, lawyer and writer, 
liberal minister of justice in <PERSON>Mr. Theodor Stolojan</PERSON>'s cabinet, 
1991-1992. 
  The conflict and tensions between these two factions and 
between them and other liberal splinter groups have inflicted, 
commentators observe, a negative image on <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>'s main liberal 
party, which the <DATE>1990</DATE> elections had earned an important number 
of seats in the Parliament that functioned until the next 
elections of <DATE>1992</DATE> when it failed to gain the minimal share of 
votes for parliamentary representation. At that time, liberal 
leaders blamed the failure on <ORGANIZATION>Radu Campeanu</ORGANIZATION>'s strong ego, who on 
the one hand decided to withdraw from the principal opposition 
bloc known as the Democratic Convention of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> (CDR) and on 
the other blundered tragically proposing the former sovereign of 
<LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>, Mihai I, who abdicated in <DATE>1947</DATE>, as candidate for 
presidency, both moves meeting popular disagreement. 
  Starting from <DATE>February 1994</DATE>, <ORGANIZATION>PNL</ORGANIZATION> has had a bi-cephalous 
leadership, one being <PERSON>Mircea Ionescu-Quintus</PERSON>, elected PNL 
president in <DATE>1993</DATE>, and the other <PERSON>Radu Campeanu</PERSON>, whom the 
"Campeanu" grouping designated as president of the <ORGANIZATION>National 
Liberal Party</ORGANIZATION> at an extraordinary congress. After this the 
story started of what the press called "the fight for the 
party's stamp" and the fight for the <LOCATION>Bucharest</LOCATION> central seat of 
the party, until the sides turned to the law for a verdict. 
  The resolution made yesterday by the <ORGANIZATION>Bucharest Municipal 
Court</ORGANIZATION> is practically the rejection of a contention lodged by the 
<ORGANIZATION>Quintus</ORGANIZATION> wing against a previous resolution. <PERSON>Mr. Quintus</PERSON>'s group 
announced last evening that they would not abandon legal actions 
until the situation of the <ORGANIZATION>PNL</ORGANIZATION> was clarified and intimated that 
many <ORGANIZATION>PNL</ORGANIZATION> branches had extended them their support. 

</TEXT>

