<H3> <TI>   PL '93 Leaders Invite Former King To Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PL '93 Leaders Invite Former King To Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204181794 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1458 GMT 12 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest</LOCATION>, ROMPRES, 12/04/1994 -- The leaders of 
the Liberal Party '93 (PL '93) have made their intention known 
to the press by issuing an "Appeal to All Romanians for 
Conciliation and <LOCATION>Concord</LOCATION>," which also runs as an "invitation" 
extended to the former sovereign of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>, <PERSON>Mihai</PERSON> I. The 
appeal is signed by 84 members of parliament representing PL 
<DATE>'93</DATE>, the <ORGANIZATION>Peasant Party</ORGANIZATION> (PNTCD), the Civic Alliance Party (PAC), 
the Hungarians' Union (<ORGANIZATION>UDMR</ORGANIZATION>), the Social Democrats (PSDR), the 
Democrats (PD-FSN), and two independent parliamentarians. It 
shows that on the religious holiday of Easter (Orthodox, 1 May) 
"King Mihai of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> must be together with all Romanians, in 
the ancestral land, as a citizen of this country, observant of 
its constitutional order." 
  The former sovereign expressed his wish to celebrate Easter 
in <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>, at <LOCATION>Timisoara</LOCATION>. 

</TEXT>

