<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Opposition Coalition Leading PDSR </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Shows Opposition Coalition Leading PDSR </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0904183494 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1651 GMT 9 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0904183494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest ROMPRES</LOCATION>, 9/4/1994 -- According to a 
public opinion poll conducted over <DATE>March 24-April 2</DATE>, the 
Democratic Convention of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> [CDR] holds the largest share 
in the political options expressed by the Romanian citizens with 
<PERCENT>24 percent</PERCENT>, followed by the ruling party, Social Democracy Party 
of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> [<ORGANIZATION>PDSR</ORGANIZATION>], with <PERCENT>21 percent</PERCENT>. The major problems are 
believed to be inflation (<PERCENT>78 percent</PERCENT>,) corruption (<PERCENT>67 percent</PERCENT>,) 
unemployment (<PERCENT>66 percent</PERCENT>,) and salary size (<PERCENT>64 percent</PERCENT>.) 
  The poll conducted by the <ORGANIZATION>Center for Urban and Regional 
Sociology</ORGANIZATION> together with <ORGANIZATION>Data Media</ORGANIZATION> ranked the other political 
parties in the public preferences as follows: Democratic Union 
of Hungarians in <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> [<ORGANIZATION>UDMR</ORGANIZATION>] <PERCENT>5 percent</PERCENT>, the <ORGANIZATION>National Romanian 
Unity Party</ORGANIZATION> [<ORGANIZATION>PUNR</ORGANIZATION>] and the <ORGANIZATION>Socialist Party of Labor</ORGANIZATION> [PSM] <PERCENT>4 
percent</PERCENT> each, the Democratic Party [PD] and the <ORGANIZATION>Greater Romania 
Party</ORGANIZATION> [PRM] <PERCENT>3 percent</PERCENT> each, and the Democratic Agrarian Party of 
<LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> [PDAR] <PERCENT>2 percent</PERCENT>. 
  The majority of the population considers that the following 
things worsened: The living standard, the observance of public 
order and law, and the people's trust in the future. 
  The social problems that should immediately be solved are: 
Curbing inflation, creation of jobs, issuance and handing over 
of property title deeds on land, and speeded-up reform and 
social protection. 
  A proportion of <PERCENT>35 percent</PERCENT> of the subjects said early 
elections were necessary, while <PERCENT>42 percent</PERCENT> pronounced themselves 
against such elections. The findings of the poll were published 
by dailies EVENIMENTUL ZILEI and <LOCATION>ROMANIA</LOCATION> LIBERA. 

</TEXT>

