<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest ROMPRES</LOCATION>, 20/6/1994 -- President <PERSON>Ion 
Iliescu</PERSON> of <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> received <DATE>Monday, 20 June</DATE>, <PERSON>Husamettin 
Cindoruk</PERSON>, the president of the <ORGANIZATION>Grand National Assembly of 
Turkey</ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON>Mr. Cindoruk</PERSON> told the press after the interview with 
the Romanian president that the main topic of their talk was the 
Turkish-Romanian cooperation at multiple levels. "President 
<PERSON>Iliescu</PERSON> told us how important the cooperation in the Black Sea 
zone is," the guest said, "and our common view is that <LOCATION>Turkey</LOCATION> 
and <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION> can ensure, by collaboration, the peace in the 
region." The president of the <ORGANIZATION>Turkish Grand National Assembly</ORGANIZATION> 
conveyed to President <PERSON>Iliescu</PERSON> [Turkish] President <PERSON>Suleyman 
Demirel</PERSON>'s invitation to visit <LOCATION>Turkey</LOCATION>. 

</TEXT>

